<br>
When the summoned focus items came out I always read the save you get (dmg, mana save etc) is a random figure.<br>
<br>
And I have to say I never really thought about it....until now, because it didnt really matter: bracelet gave more dmg - nice. ring gave shorter casting time - nice. earring lowered mana cost - nice.<br>
<br>
Now in the light of the trials which I havent passed yet (eeeks...3 attempts and always failed with 2 MObs of last wave left) I started to think about  &quot;mana management&quot;.<br>
<br>
So here's the question I got:<br>
If I equip the ring the spell description gives a casting time that is always 15% lower than the standard casting time.<br>
<br>
What about bracelet and earring?<br>
Does the bracelet always add 20% dmg or is it a random number between 0 and 20%?<br>
Does the earring always reduce the mana cost by 15% or is it a random figure between 0 and 15%?<br>
<br>
does anyone know the &quot;final&quot; answer to that? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_new2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#333333>(12/27/02 3:01:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1140.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: summoned focus items...</span><hr size=1> Not 100% sure about this, but because the ring always lowers the casting time with a fixed time, it could very well be that the earring always reduces mana use by a fixed percentage and the bracer always increases the damage (base damage or damage after resists??) by a fixed percentage.<br>
<br>
Good question, does anyone actually know this for sure or have an idea how you could test it?<br>
<br>
