><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Erollisi Marr<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Zettai Unmei Mokushiroku...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2532<br> <font color=#333333>(12/27/02 4:48:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1140.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: summoned focus items...</span><hr size=1> To the best of my knowledge, the damage focus bracer has always and still provides a random increase.<br>
<br>
Based on repeated experiments when the focus items first came out, the mana saving earring appears to be constant, or so close as makes no measurable difference.<br>
<br>
Spell haste has always been constant.<br>
<br>
I did not repeatedly test buff duration, but I have gotten inconsistant results.  A random factor would explain some of those.<br>
<br>
The reagent conservation choker is random.<br>
